                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18321018-171-off963 t18321018-171-crimeloc966"></join>. On the 11th of September I was in my counting-house, adjoining my warehouse, and I had a number of caps there - I heard somebody going out; I went out, and saw the prisoner near the door - I said Halloo! he turned round - I opened his basket, and found these caps and the paper on them, as they are now; they are mock sable, made of rabbits skins, dyed; he knew my premises - he has sold us things; I have made inquiry, and find he has been a very respectable man - I have a partner.</p>
